JSON Structure with cmdbApplicationId and cmdbApplicationDescription

application_set_data = {
    "applicationSet": f"{application_name} Application Set",  # Name of the Application Set
    "applicationName": application_name,                      # Name of the Application
    "applicationSetCmdbApplicationInstances": [
        {
            "cmdbApplicationInstanceId": "4c14231d1baf00956c95354604bcbee"  # Example instance ID
        }
    ],
    "applicationSetResourceTypes": [
        {
            "resourceType": "Resource Type 1",
            "attributes": [
                {
                    "attribute": "Attribute Type 1",
                    "dataType": "String"
                },
                {
                    "attribute": "Attribute Type 2",
                    "dataType": "Numeric"
                }
            ],
            "actions": [
                {
                    "action": "Readonly"
                }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "cmdbApplicationId": cmdb_application_id,                 # CMDB Application ID goes here
    "cmdbApplicationDescription": application_name            # Description of the CMDB Application
}

Explanation:

cmdbApplicationId: This is the unique identifier for the CMDB application you want to associate with the Application Set. It helps the system identify the specific application in the CMDB.

cmdbApplicationDescription: This is a human-readable description of the CMDB application. It is usually the application name or a brief description of what the application does.


Where to Include cmdbApplicationId:

1. cmdbApplicationId should be included at the root level of your application_set_data dictionary.


2. You retrieve this value using your get_cmdb_application_by_id function and pass it to the create_application_set_in_asset_store function.



